From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Martin Schmiedel <Martin.Schmiedel@tq-group.com>
Date: Mon, 5 May 2025 08:01:00 +0200
Subject: fix: guard u-boot.its rule against absent CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE

When CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE is absent from .config (e.g. because
CONFIG_SPL_FIT is not set), Make expands $(CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE) to
the empty string.  The guard

    ifneq ($(CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE),"")

then compares "" (empty) against the literal two-character string ""
which is NOT equal, so the condition fires.  This sets
U_BOOT_ITS := u-boot.its and creates a rule with no prerequisites,
so 'cp $<' expands to 'cp u-boot.its' and fails:

    cp: missing destination file operand after 'u-boot.its'
    make: *** [Makefile:1379: u-boot.its] Error 1

Fix: strip Kconfig-style double quotes first (the same $(subst ",,...)
idiom already used on the very next line for the prerequisite), then
compare against the empty string.  Both the absent case (expands to
empty) and the explicitly-empty case (CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE="" ->
stripped to empty) now evaluate to FALSE as intended.
---
 Makefile | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Makefile b/Makefile
index 111111111111..222222222222 100644
--- a/Makefile
+++ b/Makefile
@@ -1373,7 +1373,7 @@ u-boot.ldr.hex u-boot.ldr.srec: u-boot.ldr FORCE
 # or a generator script
 # NOTE: Please do not use this. We are migrating away from Makefile rules to use
 # binman instead.
-ifneq ($(CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE),"")
+ifneq ($(subst ",,$(CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE)),)
 U_BOOT_ITS := u-boot.its
 $(U_BOOT_ITS): $(subst ",,$(CONFIG_SPL_FIT_SOURCE))
 	$(call if_changed,copy)
-- 
